    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It feels almost... beautiful, doesn't it? The idea that there is a way to make the pain stop entirely. To have everything just go still. Like a final, graceful bow at the end of a tragedy. Is it wrong to think that there is a certain dignity in choosing to leave before the decay sets in?",
